# Frontend Admin Console Nginx Standards

This rule governs edge behavior for `Agent UI and Admin Console/nginx.conf`.
Changes here are production-impacting and must follow enterprise ingress controls.

## Required Edge Controls
- Keep Layer-7 volumetric defense at Nginx (`limit_req_zone`, `limit_conn_zone`) with NAT-safe thresholds.
- Do not move business identity quotas to Nginx. Per-user/per-tenant quotas remain in FastAPI `RateLimiterManager`.
- Preserve SSE-safe proxy behavior for `/api/agent/stream`:
  - `proxy_buffering off`
  - streaming-friendly `proxy_read_timeout` and `proxy_send_timeout`
  - forwarding headers and keep-alive-safe proxy settings
  - disable buffering paths that can delay SSE delivery

## Guardrails For Rate Limits
- Avoid low per-IP caps that penalize NATed enterprise users.
- Use edge limits to absorb abusive traffic, not to enforce authenticated product quotas.
- Any threshold change must include operational rationale in `CHANGELOG.md`.

## Validation Requirements Before Merge
- Run an Nginx syntax sanity check for this file and capture outcome.
- Confirm no route precedence regressions (`/api/agent/stream` remains above generic `/api/`).
- Report verified items and residual risks in handoff notes.

